    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛡 Threat Prevention — via MCP Gateway\n\nSame agent as the direct Threat Prevention demo, but every MCP call rides through the **Docker MCP Gateway** — ONE endpoint (`mcp-gateway:8080/mcp`), **Bearer auth**, aggregating **all** Check Point MCP servers.\n\n👉 The point to show: one credential + one endpoint fronts the whole CP MCP fleet (rate-limiting, auth, and audit in one place).",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 400
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -620,
        -60
      ],
      "name": "Sticky 78450"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### 💬 Try these\n\n- List the Threat Prevention profiles\n- Which profile is strictest and what does it activate?\n- Search IPS protections related to log4j",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 240,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
